    {
      "id": "a0631d56-d",
      "type": "header",
      "data": {
        "level": 2,
        "text": "Writing notes in Markdown"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "47423f6e-3",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "data": {
        "text": "Markdown is a lightweight markup language with plain text formatting syntax. Joplin supports a <a href=\"https://joplinapp.org/help/apps/markdown\">Github-flavoured Markdown syntax</a> with a few variations and additions."
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "c301a242-1",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "data": {
        "text": "In general, while Markdown is a markup language, it is meant to be human readable, even without being rendered. This is a simple example (you can see how it looks in the viewer panel):"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "efdf7c8e-d",
      "type": "delimiter",
      "data": {}
    },
    {
      "id": "dd960741-a",
      "type": "header",
      "data": {
        "level": 1,
        "text": "Heading"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "975198bd-e",
      "type": "header",
      "data": {
        "level": 2,
        "text": "Sub-heading"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "a2ea051f-b",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "data": {
        "text": "Paragraphs are separated by a blank line. Text attributes <i>italic</i>, <b>bold</b> and <code>monospace</code> are supported. You can create bullet lists:"
      }
    },
    {
